00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:02.040
JP SOUCHAK: If you've been
working in web development,

00:00:02.040 --> 00:00:04.870
you might ask yourself, how can
I separate myself from the pack

00:00:04.870 --> 00:00:06.240
and get recognized?

00:00:06.240 --> 00:00:08.640
Introducing the Mobile Web
Specialist Certification

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:10.860
by Google, an achievement
available to those

00:00:10.860 --> 00:00:13.950
who can demonstrate the skills
of an advanced level mobile web

00:00:13.950 --> 00:00:15.566
developer.

00:00:15.566 --> 00:00:16.940
The first step on
your journey is

00:00:16.940 --> 00:00:19.660
determining if you're
ready to take the exam.

00:00:19.660 --> 00:00:22.449
Start by learning
what the exam covers.

00:00:22.449 --> 00:00:24.490
Review the skills that
you'll need to demonstrate

00:00:24.490 --> 00:00:26.410
when taking the exam.

00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:28.180
Next, decide whether
you need training

00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:30.400
or if you're ready
to take the exam.

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:31.840
You can reference
our study guide,

00:00:31.840 --> 00:00:34.120
and training is
available online.

00:00:34.120 --> 00:00:36.880
When you're ready, sign
up and take the exam.

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:40.000
As part of the sign up,
you'll pay an exam fee.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.850
If you live in India,
you'll pay 6,500 rupees.

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:48.440
If you live outside of
India, you'll pay $99 US.

00:00:48.440 --> 00:00:50.360
After you've signed
up and paid the fee,

00:00:50.360 --> 00:00:51.830
you'll receive a
voucher that you

00:00:51.830 --> 00:00:54.530
can use to schedule the exam.

00:00:54.530 --> 00:00:56.972
The exam's a timed,
performance-based assessment

00:00:56.972 --> 00:00:58.430
in which you'll
write code to solve

00:00:58.430 --> 00:01:01.070
challenges and demonstrate
your skills in mobile web

00:01:01.070 --> 00:01:02.360
development.

00:01:02.360 --> 00:01:05.239
You'll have four hours to
finish, after which you'll

00:01:05.239 --> 00:01:07.730
submit the exam and respond
to a set of exit interview

00:01:07.730 --> 00:01:08.910
questions.

00:01:08.910 --> 00:01:10.850
If after grading
you are successful,

00:01:10.850 --> 00:01:12.850
you'll receive a digital
badge from Google

00:01:12.850 --> 00:01:15.350
and join our community of
Google Certified Mobile Web

00:01:15.350 --> 00:01:16.730
Specialists.

00:01:16.730 --> 00:01:19.010
Once you are certified,
you can share your badge

00:01:19.010 --> 00:01:22.550
on your resume,
LinkedIn, G+, Twitter,

00:01:22.550 --> 00:01:24.980
and in your email signature.

00:01:24.980 --> 00:01:27.400
Ready to start your journey?

